Nearly 1.8 million EU nationals have applied to stay in Britain after Brexit, according to figures out Wednesday. Some 1,759,400 applications had been received by European Union nationals by September 30, the Home Office said, of which 495,700 were received last month alone. READ ALSO:French Embattled EU Nominee Denies Wrongdoing In Fraud Case The countries with the most applicants were Poland with 347,300, Romania (280,600), Italy (200,700), Portugal (162,500) and Spain (115,700). Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Launched in March, the online system allows EU, wider European Economic Area and Swiss citizens residing in Britain to obtain, free of charge, settled status or pre-settled status.